Abstract: Ray Lucas, former backup quarterback on New York Jets, will start against Seattle Seahawks, while Glenn Foley, former starting quarterback for Jets, will be backup for Seahawks; photo (M)
Snippet: Ray Lucas, former backup quarterback on New York Jets, will start against Seattle Seahawks, while Glenn Foley, former starting quarterback for Jets, will be backup for Seahawks; photo (M)
LeadParagraph: In a final twist to the regular season, which shows just how unpredictable pro football has become, a former backup quarterback on the Jets will start Sunday against Seattle, while a former starting quarterback for the Jets will be the backup for the Seahawks.

Headline.Main: A Quarterback Reverse: Lucas Stars as Foley Sits
Headline.PrintHeadline: PRO FOOTBALL; A Quarterback Reverse: Lucas Stars as Foley Sits
